===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, alteration of earlier {{term|hendi||handy, skillful|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|hendiġ||skillful}} (as in {{term/t|ang|listhendiġ||skilled in art}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*handugaz||handy, skillful, nimble}}, from {{term/t|gem-pro|*handuz||hand}}, equivalent to {{suffix|hand|y|lang=en|nocat=1}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|handich||skillful, apt|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|handec|lang=gmh}}, {{term|hendec||manual, hand-held|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|hǫndugr||sc=Latinx|efficient|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐌷𐌰𐌽𐌳𐌿𐌲𐍃||tr=handugs|wise, clever|lang=got|sc=Goth}}.

